com.github.douglasorr.shared

Interface SharedArray<T>

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Collection<T>, Iterable<T>, List<T>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    TrieArray

    public interface SharedArray<T>
extends List<T>
    An array that supports shared updates in place of mutable ones. Apart from this, it behaves as a normal Java immutable List.

    Instead of using List.add, use append(Object), instead of using List.remove(n-1), use remend(), and instead of using List.set, use update(int, Object).

    Best suited to sequential containers where random reads and insertion at the end is required. Implementations offer efficient insertion at end, updates, and indexing, as well as an efficient operation for selecting a prefix sub-list.

    See SharedArrays for some less efficient, but potentially useful operations, based on this API.
